<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT/TELESCOPING - 2000, 4000, 8000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - Service Procedure
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Service Procedure</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The steering column can be removed with the steering wheel in place or removed.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0501203">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0501203" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501203" filename="../figg05/G0501203.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Steering Column Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove battery negative terminal cable.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove steering wheel if column is to be serviced. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s05012_HL0501202.xml" xrefid="hl0501202">STEERING WHEEL</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove turn signal and trailer brake controls from column.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mark position of universal joint on universal joint assembly lower shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pinch bolt that secures the steering shaft upper universal joint to the universal
                    joint assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolts, nuts and lockwashers that attach the column to the dash reinforcement.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove steering column from vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install splined end of column universal joint assembly into upper universal joint of
                    steering shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install column to mounting brackets on dash reinforcement with bolts and nuts; tighten
                    to 34 to 42 ft-lbs. (46 to 57 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install pinch bolt to secure upper universal joint to steering column and tighten until
                    non-threaded portion above plastic collar shears off.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install turn signal and trailer hand brake control to column.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install steering wheel; refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s05012_HL0501202.xml" xrefid="hl0501203">STEERING WHEEL</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect battery negative cable.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>The steering column is serviced as an assembly, and as such should not be disassembled.</para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
